{"Body": "<p>\n</p><p>After having launched a pilot episode on TV3 in early December, Glee was announced as the new resident newbie show to the channel to start this January.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Initially fettered by its seemingly close similarity to Disney&rsquo;s High School Musical, further viewing will make it clear that the show is not that similar to High School Musical after all: its jokes are more risqu&eacute;, its breaking out into song less random, its cast older and its characters more likeable.</p>\n<p>If that hasn&rsquo;t drawn you in, the soundtrack is a winner. The first episode relinquishes all singing, all dancing takes of classics like &lsquo;Rehab&rsquo; and &lsquo;Don&rsquo;t Stop Believing&rsquo;, the latter shooting straight into the top five on Irish iTunes following the pilot episode in December. &nbsp;</p>\n<p>Set in a middle of nowhere high school, this stereotype comedy follows teacher Mr. Schuester on his journey of turning his merry band of misfits into a glee club to be proud of.</p>\n<p>The first season of Glee has yet to finish airing on Fox in the US and has been met with favourable reviews and a strong following (fans of the show are known as &ldquo;Gleeks&rdquo;). &nbsp;It was also nominated for four Golden Globes and won the Favourite New TV Comedy award at this year&rsquo;s People&rsquo;s Choice Awards.</p>\n", "Imageurl": "<p>\n</p><p>After having launched a pilot episode on TV3 in early December, Glee was announced as the new resident newbie show to the channel to start this January.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Initially fettered by its seemingly close similarity to Disney&rsquo;s High School Musical, further viewing will make it clear that the show is not that similar to High School Musical after all: its jokes are more risqu&eacute;, its breaking out into song less random, its cast older and its characters more likeable.</p>\n<p>If that hasn&rsquo;t drawn you in, the soundtrack is a winner. The first episode relinquishes all singing, all dancing takes of classics like &lsquo;Rehab&rsquo; and &lsquo;Don&rsquo;t Stop Believing&rsquo;, the latter shooting straight into the top five on Irish iTunes following the pilot episode in December. &nbsp;</p>\n<p>Set in a middle of nowhere high school, this stereotype comedy follows teacher Mr. Schuester on his journey of turning his merry band of misfits into a glee club to be proud of.</p>\n<p>The first season of Glee has yet to finish airing on Fox in the US and has been met with favourable reviews and a strong following (fans of the show are known as &ldquo;Gleeks&rdquo;). &nbsp;It was also nominated for four Golden Globes and won the Favourite New TV Comedy award at this year&rsquo;s People&rsquo;s Choice Awards.</p>\n", "Thumb_nail": "http://universitytimes.ie/wp-content/uploads/2013/utlogo.jpg", "ID": "534", "Heading": "Glee set to bring joy to the high school musical genre"}